Here are **more design flaws with reasons and improvements** for each image.

## 1. Open False Ceiling (Image 1)

| Design Issue                   | Why It Is Bad                           | Suggested Improvement                               |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| Exposed HVAC ducts             | Poor appearance and difficult to clean  | Install ceiling panels with removable access panels |
| Exposed electrical cables      | Electrical safety risk                  | Route cables inside cable trays and conduits        |
| No maintenance access planning | Frequent ceiling removal damages panels | Provide dedicated inspection hatches                |
| Dust accumulation              | Reduces indoor air quality              | Regular cleaning and sealed ceiling system          |
| Visible building services      | Reduces aesthetic quality               | Conceal services within suspended ceiling           |
| Uneven ceiling finish          | Gives unfinished appearance             | Maintain uniform ceiling alignment                  |

